{"cursor":"12274","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox scientist\n| name = image =  image_size = alt = caption = birth_date\n| = birth_place = Irvington, NJ, USA death_date =  death_place = resting_place =\n| resting_place_coordinates =  residence = New Jersey citizenship =\n| United States nationality = fields = workplaces = Bell Labs alma_mater =\n| Wellesley B.A., Yale Ph.D. thesis_title = An Analysis of Contrary-to-\n| Fact Conditional Sentences thesis_url = thesis_year =\n| 1951 doctoral_advisor = academic_advisors = doctoral_students =\n| notable_students = known_for = Computerized system for phone traffic author_abbrev_bot = author_abbrev_zoo = influences =\n| influenced = awards = National Inventors Hall of Fame, 2008 Wellesley alumni achievement award\n| signature =  signature_alt = website = \n| footnotes = spouse =\n}}\n\n'Dr. Erna Schneider Hoover' (born June 19, 1926) is an American mathematician\nnotable for inventing a computerized telephone switching method which\n\"revolutionized modern communication\" according to several reports. {{cite news |author= Amy Ellis Nutt |title= Fame calls on 2\ntitans of telephony in NJ |work= The Star-Ledger |date= June 18, 2008 |url=\nhttp://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2008/06/fame_calls_on_2_titans_of_tele.html\n|accessdate= 2012-06-05 }} {{cite news |title= Hall of\nFame -- induction info |work= National Inventors Hall of Fame (invent.org)\n|date= 2008 |url=\nhttp://www.invent.org/2008induction/1_3_08_induction_hoover.asp |accessdate= 2012-06-\n05 }} It prevented system overloads by monitoring call center traffic and\nprioritizing tasks on phone switching systems to enable\nmore robust service during peak calling times. At Bell\nLaboratories where she worked for over 32 years, {{cite news\n|author= CALVIN SIMS |title= BELL LABS: ADAPTING TO MONOPOLY'S END |work= The\nNew York Times |date= March 09, 1987 |url= http://www.nytimes.com/1987/03/09/business/bell-labs-adapting-to-monopoly-s-\nend.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |accessdate= 2012-06-05 }} Hoover was\ndescribed as an important pioneer for women in the field of computer\ntechnology. {{cite news |title= Erna Hoover -- Biography\n|work= World of Computer Science |date= 2012 |url= http://www.bookrags.com/biography/erna-hoover-\nwcs |accessdate= 2012-06-17 }} She was awarded one of the first patents\nfor computer software. She was elected as a member of the\nNational Inventors Hall of Fame in 2008.\n","linknr":265,"url":"Erna_Schneider_Hoover","recorded":1374763511,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Erna_Schneider_Hoover&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Erna_Schneider_Hoover&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Irvington,_New_Jersey","/wiki/New_Jersey","/wiki/United_States","#cite_note-tws2E2114-1","/wiki/New_Jersey","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Bell_Laboratories","/wiki/Alma_mater","/wiki/Wellesley_College","/wiki/Yale_University","/wiki/Thesis","#cite_note-tws2Q111-2","#cite_note-tws2Q111-2","/wiki/National_Inventors_Hall_of_Fame","#cite_note-hof-3","#cite_note-tws2Q111-2","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Mathematician","#cite_note-tws2E2112-4","#cite_note-tws2E2114-1","#cite_note-tws2E2112-4","/wiki/Telephone_exchange","#cite_note-tws2E211